Author: DAWSON
Vol / Page: 121
Edition:
Quote:  [The second major forest type] is dominated in the canopy ... by one or more species of southern beech (<i>Nothofagus</i> ), a genus restricted to the southern hemisphere, but nevertheless related to the ... true beeches (<i>Fagus</i>) of the northern hemisphere. ... However, despite the clear differences between the two genera, it has become customary in New Zealand to refer to our species as `beech' without qualification.
